# Build context = .devcontainer/ (compose `context: .`). Default-deny: ignore the
# whole context, then re-include ONLY the paths the Dockerfile actually COPYs.
# This keeps the generated .env (Postgres password) and other host-only config
# (compose.yaml, devcontainer.json, gen-*.sh, db-init/, db-backups/) OUT of the
# build context entirely — they cannot leak into an image layer or `docker history`.
# It also shrinks the context, so unrelated edits don't bust the build cache.
#
# When you add a new COPY source to the Dockerfile, add a matching `!` line here.
*

# Dockerfile + its COPY sources (keep in sync with the COPY lines in Dockerfile)
!Dockerfile
!install-tools.sh
!init-firewall.sh
!entrypoint.sh
!seed-claude.sh
!init-cron.sh
!log-event.sh
!crontab-reload
!crontab-edit
!home/
!seed/CLAUDE.md
!seed/crontab
!config/extra-allowlist.txt
!config/extra-allowlist.txt.example

# Belt-and-suspenders: never ship the DB secret even if a re-include above widens.
.env
